      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FLASH ON BY (2) had a low draw last time over 520m at Wentworth Park but was in traffic and fell. No luck latest and worth another chance. SCRUTINISE (1) had the drop on the lead and went on to be beaten 2 lengths into third (31.22) at Wagga in a Grade 5 over 525m. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Expected to be in this for a long way. PELOPONNESE (4) started big odds but ran a huge race last time when finishing 2nd over 457m at this track (25.69)in Grade 3/4. Scored at Wagga in weaker company the previous run. Form at the trip sound including seven wins. Has performed well from this box with a win and five minor placings to her name from 11 starts. Expected to feature again. HAVOC TWO (7) missed the placings here last start but is well-placed to turn the form around.",
